ole civilizations on earth and beyond. They offer players a dizzying array of dystopian scenarios in which to build and invent, cooperate with others (through other players, NPCs, or AI) to survive another day. Contributors show how video games focus attention, hone visuospatial skills, and shape cognitive control and physical reflexes and thus have the power to participate in the larger context of radical, activist artworks that challenge destructive hegemonic structures as methods of human conditioning, coping, and creating.\u003c\/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eWith contributions from Anna Anthropy, Tiffany Funk, Martin Zeilinger, Elizabeth LaPensée, Andrew Bailey, Michael Anthony DeAnda, Luisa Salvador Dias, Michael Paramo, and Treva Michelle Legassie. \u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.12471206\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.12471206","language":"eng","modified":"2024-06-16T08:19:55Z","published":"2018-01-01","publisher":"Amherst College Press","subject":["Game Studies","Digital \u0026 Media Studies"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/6395w982v/download","type":"application/pdf"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/6395w982v/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/9019s5051/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/9019s5051/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/9019s5051/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/9019s5051/full/800,/0/default.jpg","width":800,"type":"image/jpeg"}]},{"metadata":{"@type":"http://schema.org/EBook","title":"Video Game Art Reader: Volume 1","author":["Funk, Tiffany","Reed, Michael"],"belongsTo":{"series":"Video Game Art Read