ce how what was a largely white school throughout the interwar years begins diversifying its student demographics after World War II and the War in Vietnam. The histories told here illuminate how Amherst has contended with slavery, wars, religion, coeducation, science, curriculum, town and gown relations, governance, and funding during its two centuries of existence. Through Amherst’s engagement with educational improvement in light of these historical undulations, it continually affirms both the vitality and the utility of a liberal arts education.\u003c\/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eWith contributions from Gary J. Kornblithk, David W. Wills, Frederick E. Hoxie, Trent Maxey, Nicholas L. Syrett, Wendy H. Bergoffen, Martha Saxton, Rick López, Matthew Alexander Randolph, Daniel Levinson Wilk, K. Ian Shin, David S. Reynolds, Jane F. Thrailkill, Julie Dobrow, Richard F. Teichgraeber III, Debby Applegate, Michael E. Jirik, Bruce Laurie, Molly Michelmore, and Christian G. Appy. \u003c\/p\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003eAn auto-narrated audiobook is available via the \u0026quot;Download\u0026quot; button above.\u003c\/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.11873533\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.11873533","language":"eng","modified":"2024-10-09T08:20:43Z","published":"2020-01-01","publisher":"Amherst College","subject":"History"},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/fx719p52m/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/fx719p52m/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/bn999876c/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/m326m387f/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/